    },
    {
      "text": "Baby T-Rex is a platform game developed by Beam Software for Game Boy. It was released in 1993 in Europe by Laser Beam Entertainment, Beam's publishing arm. The same underlying game was released under alternate titles each adapting a different intellectual property: Agro Soar in Australia, Bamse in Sweden, and We're Back! A Dinosaur's Story in North America, where it was published by Hi Tech Expressions.\nThe following year Beam released a follow-up, Radical Rex, for Super NES, Sega Genesis and Sega CD, which in 2022 was bundled with the Game Boy game in a compilation for various platforms.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
